**Origins of the Multiverse Theory**

While the idea of multiple universes dates back to ancient Greek philosophy Plato's concept of the "Many-Worlds Interpretation," the modern multiverse hypothesis gained traction in the late 20th century.
The concept of the multiverse can be traced back to ancient Greece where philosopher Aristotle hypothesized about multiple coexisting worlds.
